data-triple-N3.o: "The Boston Globe (and the Boston Sunday Globe) is an American daily newspaper based in Boston, Massachusetts. The Boston Globe has been owned by The New York Times Company since 1993. Its chief print rival is the Boston Herald. The Boston Globe has won 21 Pulitzer Prizes. The New York Times Company, who owns the Globe, announced on February 20, 2013, it is selling the paper and its related assets."@en
